# Code Formatting

## After Making Changes

After completing code changes, run `pnpm format` to ensure consistent formatting across the codebase.

## Formatting Configuration

This project uses Prettier for code formatting. The configuration is defined in `.prettierrc.json` at the project root.

Key behaviors:
- Run `pnpm format` after making code changes
- Run `pnpm lint --fix` to auto-fix linting issues
- The pre-commit hook will format staged files automatically

**Source of truth**: `.prettierrc.json`

> **Note**: This rule assumes pnpm + Prettier. If your project uses a different package manager or formatter, override this rule with a project-specific `.cursor/rules/code-formatting.mdc`.
